Aim

To perform arithmetic operations using 8051.

Theory
Arithmetic operations are performed using ALU
Accumulator stores result
Instructions: ADD, SUBB, MUL, DIV
Carry flag indicates overflow
MUL stores result in A and B
DIV gives quotient and remainder
Used in embedded systems
Simulator Used

EdSim51

Code
ORG 0000H

; ADD
MOV A, #25H
MOV R0, #12H
ADD A, R0

; SUB
MOV A, #50H
MOV R1, #20H
SUBB A, R1

; MUL
MOV A, #12H
MOV B, #05H
MUL AB

; DIV
MOV A, #40H
MOV B, #08H
DIV AB

SJMP $
END
Observation
ADD → A = 37H
SUB → A = 30H
MUL → A = 3CH, B = 00H
DIV → A = 08H, B = 00H
All operations correct
Conclusion

Thus, arithmetic operations were successfully implemented and verified.
